.\" Man page for pico_ctl
.TH PICO_CTL 1 "April 2026" "pico-ctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pico_ctl \- all-in-one CLI for managing a Raspberry Pi Pico over USB serial
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pico_ctl
.RB [ \-\-port
.IR PORT ]
.RB [ \-\-sync\-rtc ]
.IR command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pico_ctl
manages a Raspberry Pi Pico running MicroPython over USB serial.
Upload files, backup, monitor, reset, and inspect \(em all from a single command.
.PP
If no subcommand is given, defaults to
.BR info .
.PP
The Pico is auto-detected by USB vendor ID (0x2E8A).
Works with Pico, Pico\ W, Pico\ 2, and Pico\ 2\ W.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Serial port to use (e.g.\&
.IR /dev/ttyACM0 ).
Auto-detected if omitted.
.TP
.B \-\-sync\-rtc
Sync the device RTC to host time on connect.
Can also be enabled by setting the environment variable
.BR PICO_SYNC_RTC=1 .
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Inspect
.TP
.B info
Show firmware version, board ID, CPU frequency, RAM, flash usage, and file listing.
This is the default command when none is specified.
.TP
.B ls \fR[\fIPATH\fR] [\fB\-\-flat\fR]
List files on the Pico.
.I PATH
defaults to
.BR / .
Listing is recursive by default; use
.B \-\-flat
(or
.BR \-f )
for a single-directory listing.
.TP
.B tree \fR[\fIPATH\fR]
Show a file tree with SHA256 hashes.
.I PATH
defaults to
.BR / .
.TP
.B cat \fIPATH\fR
Print the contents of a file on the Pico.
.TP
.B edit \fIPATH\fR
Download a file from the Pico, open it in
.BR $EDITOR ,
and upload it back if changed.
.TP
.B cp \fISRC\fR \fIDST\fR
Copy files to or from the Pico.
Prefix a path with
.B :
to indicate the Pico filesystem (e.g.\&
.IR :config.py ).
.TP
.B df
Show flash and RAM usage summary.
.TP
.B ports
List available serial ports on the host.
.SS Execute
.TP
.B exec \fICODE\fR \fR[\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR]
Run arbitrary MicroPython code on the Pico.
.I TIMEOUT
defaults to 10 seconds.
.TP
.B run \fIFILE\fR \fR[\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR] [\fB\-\-detach\fR]
Run a
.I .py
file on the Pico and stream output.
.I TIMEOUT
defaults to 180 seconds.
Use
.B \-\-detach
(or
.BR \-d )
to launch the script and disconnect; the Pico keeps running.
.TP
.B mip \fIPACKAGE\fR \fR[\fB\-\-target\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR]
Install a MicroPython package via
.BR mip .
Requires WiFi on the Pico.
.I PACKAGE
is a package spec such as
.I github:user/repo
or a package name.
.B \-\-target
sets the install directory on the Pico (default:
.IR /lib ).
.I TIMEOUT
defaults to 60 seconds.
.TP
.B repl
Open an interactive MicroPython REPL session.
Press
.B Ctrl+]
to exit.
.SS File Management
.TP
.B upload \fR[\fILOCAL PICO\fR ...] [\fB\-\-dir\fR \fILOCAL_DIR PICO_PREFIX\fR] [\fB\-\-src\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Upload files and directories to the Pico.
.RS
.TP
.I "LOCAL PICO ..."
Positional pairs of local path and Pico destination path.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dir " " "\fILOCAL_DIR PICO_PREFIX\fR"
Upload a directory tree, preserving structure under
.IR PICO_PREFIX .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-src " " \fIDIR\fR
Upload all
.I .py
files from
.I DIR
to the Pico root.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be uploaded without transferring.
.RE
.IP
After uploading
.I .py
files, the module cache on the Pico is automatically cleared.
.TP
.B sync \fILOCAL_DIR\fR \fIPICO_PREFIX\fR \fR[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Upload only changed files (by size comparison).
Use
.B \-\-dry\-run
(or
.BR \-n )
to preview.
.TP
.B backup \fR[\fB\-o\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB\-f\fR \fIPATH\fR ...] [\fB\-d\fR \fIPICO_DIR\fR] [\fB\-l\fR]
Download files from the Pico to a local directory.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIDIR\fR
Local directory to save files (default:
.IR backup/ ).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-files " " "\fIPATH\fR ..."
Specific Pico paths to download (default: all).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dir " " \fIPICO_DIR\fR
Download only files under this Pico directory.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List files on the Pico without downloading.
.RE
.TP
.B rm \fIPATH\fR \fR[\fB\-r\fR]
Delete a file or directory from the Pico.
Use
.B \-r
(or
.BR \-\-recursive )
to delete a directory and all its contents.
.SS Device Control
.TP
.B reset
Soft-reset the Pico (restarts
.IR main.py ).
.TP
.B hard
Hard reset via
.BR machine.reset() .
.TP
.B bootsel
Enter BOOTSEL mode for
.I .uf2
firmware flashing.
The Pico disconnects from serial and appears as a USB drive.
.TP
.B rtc \fR[\fB\-\-set\fR]
Get or set the device real-time clock.
Without
.BR \-\-set ,
prints the current RTC time.
With
.B \-\-set
(or
.BR \-s ),
syncs the device RTC to the host clock.
.SS Monitor
.TP
.B monitor \fR[\fB\-t\fR \fISECONDS\fR] [\fB\-m\fR \fIMARKER\fR ...]
Soft-reset and stream boot output.
.I SECONDS
defaults to 45.
.B \-\-markers
(or
.BR \-m )
sets success strings to watch for (default:
.IR "Display updated" ", "
.IR "No change" ", "
.IR "Free mem" ).
.TP
.B watch \fR[\fB\-t\fR \fISECONDS\fR] [\fB\-\-reset\fR]
Attach to serial output without resetting.
.I SECONDS
defaults to 0 (indefinite).
Use
.B \-\-reset
(or
.BR \-r )
to soft-reset before watching.
Press
.B Ctrl+C
to detach; the Pico continues running.
.SH SIGNALS
All commands handle
.B SIGINT
(Ctrl+C) cleanly:
.IP \(bu 2
Streaming commands
.RB ( run ", " monitor ", " watch )
detach from serial; the Pico continues running.
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-step commands
.RB ( upload ", " sync ", " backup ", " "rm \-r" )
stop and report partial progress.
.IP \(bu 2
All other commands exit immediately.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PICO_SYNC_RTC
Set to
.B 1
to automatically sync the device RTC on every connection (equivalent to
.BR \-\-sync\-rtc ).
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used by the
.B edit
subcommand to choose the text editor.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /dev/ttyACM0
Default serial device on Linux when a single Pico is connected.
.TP
.I COM3
Typical serial port on Windows.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (no Pico found, timeout, file not found, etc.).
.SH EXAMPLES
Show device info (default command):
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl
.fi
.RE
.PP
Upload a directory tree:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl upload \-\-dir ../pico\-paper\-lib /pico_paper_lib
.fi
.RE
.PP
Sync only changed files:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl sync ../pico\-paper\-lib /pico_paper_lib \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Install a package via mip:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl mip github:jonbrefe/pico\-paper\-lib
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run a script and watch output:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl run test_all.py \-\-timeout 300
.fi
.RE
.PP
Launch and detach (Pico keeps running):
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl run main.py \-\-detach
.fi
.RE
.PP
Copy a file from Pico to local:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl cp :config.py ./config_backup.py
.fi
.RE
.PP
Interactive REPL:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl repl
.fi
.RE
.PP
Monitor boot with custom markers:
.PP
.RS
.nf
pico_ctl monitor \-\-timeout 60 \-\-markers "WiFi connected" "Ready"
.fi
.RE
.SH COMPATIBILITY
Works with all Raspberry Pi Pico variants: Pico, Pico\ W, Pico\ 2, Pico\ 2\ W.
Requires MicroPython firmware on the Pico (tested with v1.28.0).
.PP
On WSL2, USB passthrough via
.B usbipd-win
is required.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at <https://github.com/jonbrefe/pico\-ctl/issues>.
